{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"547ee24e-d45f-41cd-9048-6832ba1bb79e","content":"**Exit code 8** means \"no tests were discovered.\" Microsoft.Testing.Platform treats this as an error by default, unlike VSTest which returned 0.\n\nThe fix is the MSBuild property added to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>false</TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>\n```\n\nThis tells the test runner to exit with **0** (success) when zero tests are found, restoring the VSTest behavior. If you have many test projects, you can set this in a shared `Directory.Build.props` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4eb1c9e7-c935-4273-9a8b-6e4981c85173","outputTokens":139},"id":"a0ca8382-a559-4ea9-9bbc-6e0bd1b14981","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:47:18.956Z","parentId":"8dd1ef59-6b7e-443d-b988-3f1ab6196c59"}
